The paper deals with energy harvesting in a multi-user MIMO system with artificial noise transmission, which involves optimization of transmit beamforming matrix, AN covariance matrix, and power splitting ratio. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper primarily focuses on optimization techniques for energy harvesting in a communication system, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories.
